result.execSummary:
The defendant Shana L. Hamm was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).
  • Possess w/Intent-THC (<=200 grams) [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
If revoked the defendant has 5 days credit for time served. Defendant was ordered to report immediately to the probation and parole office.
Concurrent with: Probation is concurrent on Ct 3 and Ct 4 as are the conditions thereof unless otherwise specified.

miscConds.notes: The defendant is to submit to an Alcohol and Other Drug Assessment (AODA) and follow the recommendations, releasing the findings to the agent.

Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample, within 48 hours, for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions. Defendant is to pay costs, fines, surcharges or fees directly to and will be collected by the Clark County Clerk of Court. Defendant granted payment plan of $25.00 per month to begin 10/01/2022
The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  Defendant is to comply with any CHIPS/Social Services cases.

Defendant shall not be in the presence or possession of drugs or drug paraphernalia, or consume any medication or drug except as may be specifically prescribed by a licensed Wisconsin medical professional for defendant, and then shall be taken only as prescribed. The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement officer.

Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request 
Defendant is to participate in Clark County Recovery Court, if he successfully finishes the program he may ask for early discharge after 2 years, if agent believes it is appropriate.

timeConds.notes: Jail sentence is stayed until further order of the Court. Jail sentence is on Ct 3 only.
